<Content>A good place from which to explore SF--be prepared for some noise though. The Hotel Whitcomb has a great location and we found the staff incredibly helpful. Location: Right on Market Street so you just walk out the door and wait for the F trolly down to the waterfront ($1.50 a person, have the correct change). 4-5 blocks from some good shopping. You need to walk a bit to find a place to eat (unless you want Burger King, which is across the street or the Hotel Restaurant). Starbucks is right next door, hooray!!! Not a bad drive to the airport either.Staff: Great. We were behind one person in the Guest Services line and someone (concierge I think) came running over to assist us. When he couldn鈥檛 answer our question he took us to someone who could. Very attentive. Also, when there was an argument outside our room at 3am I called the front desk and they had someone up there pronto. We had no wait for check in or check out.Parking: I鈥檓 glad my husband was driving because I found the parking a bit stressful and confusing. We managed however. Rooms: My only complaint. It鈥檚 an old hotel so guests need to be understanding. Having said that, I鈥檇 like to let you know what to expect. The bathrooms are tiny鈥揑鈥檓 pretty thin and I have no idea how a larger person would fit between the toilet and sink. It鈥檚 almost impossible to change clothes in the bathroom (which I needed to do since I was travelling with my son). The walls are also incredibly thin. We were 5 doors down from the ice machine but heard it everytime someone got ice. Every conversation that took place in the halls could be heard too. My husband, son and I definitely were woken up several times a night because of all the noise. Not a big deal but I think it鈥檚 worth passing along on this site.A nice place from which to explore San Francisco. 
